cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CG, cs.NA, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the problem of localizing a source using TDOA measurements from three receivers, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper involves the study of the TDOA map, which encodes information about the source location. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The paper computes the Cartesian equation of the bifurcation curve, which is a geometric object related to the TDOA map. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper may involve numerical methods to compute the bifurcation curve and its asymptotic lines. 
- cs.DS (Dynamical Systems): The paper may involve the study of the dynamics of the TDOA map and its bifurcations.
